rules:
  # Router Configuration
  - Use the router configuration in `/src/router/_routerConfig.js`
  - Follow the established route structure with meta properties
  - Use route guards for authentication and permissions
  - Implement proper route parameters and query handling

  # Route Structure
  - Use nested routes for complex page structures
  - Follow the established route naming conventions
  - Use proper route meta properties for permissions and titles
  - Implement proper route parameter handling

  # Navigation Patterns
  - Use programmatic navigation with `this.$router.push()`
  - Use route parameters for dynamic routing
  - Implement proper route query handling
  - Use the established navigation patterns

  # Route Guards
  - Use beforeEach guard for authentication checks
  - Implement proper permission-based routing
  - Use the established route guard patterns
  - Handle route redirects properly

  # Route Meta Properties
  - Use meta properties for route configuration
  - Implement proper permission checking
  - Use title and label properties for navigation
  - Follow the established meta property patterns

  # Dynamic Routes
  - Use dynamic route parameters properly
  - Implement proper route parameter validation
  - Use the established dynamic routing patterns
  - Handle route parameter changes properly

